Date: Fri, 14 Aug 1998 15:23:00 -0600
From: Leslie Tengelsen <tengelse@idhw.state.id.us>

Idaho is also reporting an apparent increase in aseptic meningitis cases
throughout the lower [southern counties. During all of 1997 8 viral
meningitis cases were reported. Since mid-July 1998 more than 35 cases have
been reported to the Idaho Department of Health and Welfare. New cases are
continuing to occur throughout southern and central Idaho. Although the
etiologic agent remains unknown for the majority of cases, two unique stool
samples were presumptive for echovirus-30. A third echovirus isolate was
grown from CSF, typing is pending. Sample testing and verification
continues within Idaho and also at CDC.
--
Leslie Ann Tengelsen, Ph.D., D.V.M.
Assistant State Epidemiologist
Idaho State Department of Health and Welfare
Boise, ID 83720
TEL: (208) 334-5939
FAX: (208) 332-7346
e-mail: tengelse@idhw.state.id.us
